Pin Outs for the Microcontroller 

// Description
// PWM/Analog pins -> 2-14
// 5V tolerant pins -> 10-21
// All other digital pins are 3.3V tolerant 


// Controlling Parts -> For Servos/ESCs map from 0 - 4096 
Pin 2 ESC_1    // Speed controller 1 -> for automatic setting of the ESC we can program the the ESC to be high for a second or so and then set it low so it can do it automatically.
Pin 3 ESC_2    // Speed Controller 2
Pin 5 Servo_1 // Servo 1
Pin 6 Servo_2 // Servo 2
Pin 10 Camera 
Pin 11 TX // For Wi-Fi Board
Pin 12 RX // For Wi-Fi Board

*note : pin 4 doesn't work for now :/
//Service indicators

Pin 13 LED_1 // Camera_on
Pin 14 LED_2 // ESC_1 on
Pin 15 LED_3 // ESC_2 on
Pin 16 LED_4 // Servo_1 on
Pin 17 LED_5  // Servo_2 on
Pin 18 LED_6  // Drive_motor_1 on
Pin 19 LED_7  // Drive_Motor_2 on
Pin 20 LED_8  // Steering_Motor_1 on
Pin 21 LED_9  // Steering_Motor_2 on
Pin 22 LED_10 // Pressure_Actuator on

//Camera 
//We have the camera set on Channel 1 
//And the transceiver on Channel 1 Band E

//Dynamixel Motors : Running on Protocol 1.0 servos have to plugged in while updating micro controller
//ID_2 & ID_0 -> Are on drive mode
//ID_1 & ID_3 -> Are on Joint mode/steering mode
//            -> 2048 = 180 degrees of rotation 
//            -> 1024 = 90 degrees of rotation 
// note on code
// For forward motion:
// Dxl.writeWord(ID,Moving_Speed, 600)
//               ^      ^          ^
//               id   protocol    speed 
//               of   change      
//              motor /RPMs

// For Reverse Motion:
// Dxl.WriteWord( ID, Moving_Speed, 600|0x600)
//                 ^       ^            ^
//                ID     same as      reverse 
//                of     before       command
//              motor
